Rating: 3
To answer A Cook on 10/26/01 Mario Battali was born in Seattle, Washington. And I too cannot understand the public's obsession with adding sugar to tomatoe sauce. Fresh tomatoes are already sweet and if using canned tomatoes I would recommend finding an Italian market that stocks San Marzano tomatoes. That is not a brand name, it is a style of tomatoe, sweet, rich and low in acid. Both of my parents came from Italy and my mom (and every other Italian cook I know) added sweetness to the sauce by adding chopped carrots. Adding a sweet wine, such as Marsala or even domestic Reisling will also "sweeten" the sauce. Me? I like the acidic taste. To Corrinne, who wondered why all the salt: The salt goes into the pot of boiling water to season the pasta. It is NOT added to the sauce.

